We are looking to hire a results-driven Data Scientist with production-level ML experience and strong cloud skills to join our team.

Responsibilities:

Deliver full-cycle machine learning solutions, including exploratory data analysis (EDA), model training and tuning, feature engineering, model validation and interpretation;

Work with large-scale datasets in Databricks / Spark environments;

Deploy models to production using MLflow / MLOps pipelines;

Build dashboards and data visualizations (Power BI, Tableau);

Operate in cloud-based environments (Azure, AWS, or GCP) using storage, pipelines, orchestration tools;

Participate in client meetings, translate business problems into ML tasks, present and defend models;

Maintain and retrain models as needed.

Requirements:

5+ years of experience in Data Science / ML roles;

Deployed ML models into production, not just POCs or academic projects;

Can explain architecture and model logic to non-technical stakeholders;

Understanding of the full ML lifecycle — from raw data to dashboard;

English B2 level and higher;

Tech Stack:

Languages: Python (pandas, numpy, scikit-learn, matplotlib), SQL

Platforms: Azure, AWS, GCP, Databricks

Tools: MLflow, Spark, Synapse Analytics, Power BI, Tableau

Methods: classification, regression, clustering, time series

Processes: CI/CD, MLOps, Git, Jira, Agile/Scrum

Nice to also have:

Experience with Generative AI, NLP, LLMs

Familiarity with Spark SQL / Delta Lake

Background in consulting or multi-domain project work

Conditions:

Official employment under the Labor Code of Kazakhstan

Remote format with an option to work from the office

International projects and team

О НАС:

Наша команда Data Science и Аналитики данных активно развивается и расширяется, в связи с чем мы ищем сильного инженера, который сможет построить окружение, в котором будут жить и развиваться сервисы, в т.ч. у которых под капотом алгоритмы ML.

ЧТО НУЖНО БУДЕТ ДЕЛАТЬ:

